pth. Through a cross-cultural consideration of script obsolescence in Mesoamerica and Mesopotamia and by analogy to language death in speech communities, a model of domain-bydomain shift and obsolescence of the scripts of the Egyptian writing system is proposed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aHandschriften. 4aPapyrologie. 4aRömisches Ägypten.  aOrthographic Depth.  aScript Domains.  aScript Obsolescence.  aScript Shift.0 cEPUBz97831107684800 cprintz978311076724740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076843540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110768435423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110768435/original  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK